NIGHT STRIKER was pinballed between foes at the start, recovered to track the contesting front pair down the backside, crept closer to the leader with five sixteenths to go and could not pose a threat running one paced down the stretch for a minor share. TEAPARTYTODAY was off slowly on the break to trail down the backside, could not make any headway through the turn and showed some late energy passing tired runners down the lane. SCREEN LEGEND broke outwards on the start, was hustled inside forcing the pace down the backside, had nothing more to offer giving way pressing up front by midturn and emptied out at the furlong marker. CHIEF LIONHART stalked outside near the rear down the back straight, made little impression running around the bend and lacked a rally down the stretch. HURRICANE DESHAMBO had one rival beaten down the backside, could not gain on challengers throughout the turn and never was a factor in the stretch drive.

MR. MARSHALL assumed command at the start, dictated the pace unchallenged around the bend, opened up mildly at the top of the stretch but was no match for the winner late but comfortably bested the rest at the wire. RELOAD BULLET travelled in mid-pack on the outside down the back straight, was asked at the three furlong pole, offered little run and finished up willingly while on the wrong lead throughout the stretch. VERY DEBONAIRE stalked three deep near the back in the early going, made some progress three wide outside of horses through the turn, swung out widest in the seven path at the top of the lane but could not offer a finish to the wire. JMR SPEEDY ESCAPE hesitated on the break, was then hustled to prompt the pace outside by the half, was urged left handed trying to keep pace with the leader midway on the turn, could not rally with others on either side in upper stretch and faltered in the final furlong. HARDWARE GAP brushed the gate on the start, tracked three deep outside at the half, chased the frontrunner around the turn, was in the hunt four wide at the top of the lane, could not go on and retreated by mid-stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FAIRWAY TO HEAVEN tracked the threesome outside down the backstretch, edged closer three wide outside rivals on the turn, pounced five wide turning for home, seized control at the eighth pole and held on while drifting out under left handed urging near the wire. LAKEFIELD stalked near the back on the inside, rallied while in hand on the fence midway around the bend, shifted outside in the four path gaining momentum at the top of the lane, had clear run outside at the furlong pole and was pushed out driving to the finish line to best the rest. INDY ONE pressed the pace four wide deepest outside down the backstretch, bid three wide outside horses at the quarter pole, battled determinedly three wide in upper stretch and finished up well to be a clear third at the wire. HANLAN had a slow start on the break, settled in mid-pack on the rail along the backstretch, was coaxed at the three furlong pole closing the gap on the fence through the turn and willingly ran down the lane to settle on the fringes in the end. PEOPLE ARE PEOPLE was hustled down the back straight chasing the pacesetter, continued to keep in close range on the leader into the turn, bid two wide between runners in upper stretch, could not go on with others closing in by mid-stretch and faded in the final furlong. FAST AND READY prompted three deep between horses down the backside, was throttled back being shuffled at the seven sixteenth marker, kept up to the frontrunners through the turn, angled outside six wide for the drive and finished up evenly down the stretch. MONDAY MORNING travelled in midfield outside of runners in the early going, kept pace the leaders around the oval, shifted inwards in mid-stretch but could not get involved driving to the finish line. ROAR OF THE CROWD was slow to begin, had one rival beaten down the backstretch, made no progress through the turn and showed some energy to pass weary runners in the stretch. FOREST FLASH stalked near the back outside of horses down the backside, came under a ride midway on the turn, could not quicken with others and did not make a presence in the stretch running. FRAC RIGHT took command from the start, set the fractions through the turn inside, was collared outside at the quarter pole, offered little resistance and wilted on the fence by the furlong marker. BLUE MONTJEU broke with the field but was void of early speed and trailed down the backstretch, could not catch up with the pack around the turn and was not a factor in the drive to the wire. RACE.FOOTNOTES: JIMMIES BIG DAY tracked in behind the leading pair and inside a foe, found room inside at the top of the stretch, shot through and cleared. FABLED PRINCE settled off the pace near but off the inside, moved out making a sweeping move outside foes six wide, loomed a threat but was only second best. QUIET INTENT settled off the pace inside, shifted out past the five-sixteenths about three wide then wider still in upper stretch, kicked on to get up for show honors late. UMNEYAAT was very lightly bumped at the start, raced about mid-division in a strung-out field, gained late inside. CLASSIC DANCER broke sharply, ceded the early lead content to stalk from outside, went about three to four wide, evened out. ROOKIE RADAR raced off the inside, moved out seven wide turning for home, ran on mildly. DREAM ON BABY got away slowly, was outpaced early, saved ground on the turn, improved inside. NONNO'S LITTLE BOY broke a step slowly, swung six wide into upper stretch, needed more late. AMBER LIGHT dueled outside two to three wide, gave way. KINETIC STONE dueled inside, drifted out a bit leaving the turn, came up empty. GUARD OF HONOUR was not a factor.
